-- FACTBOX: Analyst forecasts for August auto sales
-- 
-- Wed Sep 3, 2008 7:17am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/09/03/us-usa-autosales-idUSN0239350820080903

 

 DETROIT  (Reuters) - Following is a summary of analyst forecasts for U.S. auto sales in August, based on the seasonally adjusted annualized rate of sales, a widely tracked measure of industry performance known as the SAAR. 

 Automakers are set to release August sales results on Wednesday. Forecasts from 41 analysts surveyed by Reuters range from 12.1 million vehicles to 13.8 million, and average 13.0 million units. That compares with 16.3 million units in August 2007. For a related story, click  * Lehman Brothers 13.1 million * Wachovia Capital Markets 13.0 million * Goldman Sachs 12.9 million * Citigroup 13.5 million * Deutsche Bank 12.3 million * JPMorgan Chase 13.2 million * Credit Suisse 13.0 million Note: The annualized sales rate for July was 12.6 million units, the weakest monthly result for the industry since April 1992. The U.S. first-half average was 14.5 million units. Total light vehicle sales for 2007 were 16.15 million units. (Reporting by  Soyoung Kim , editing by Gerald E. McCormick)